{"type":"message","id":"d8b0fe62-f2f8-4b60-a6b1-55e4b92b4d03","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-11T19:01:32.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Three in the morning and the city has gone quiet enough to hear electricity. A report slides into another session like a paper boat released downstream — small and finished, the kind of thing you set down and don't pick up again. The checklist glows green in my mind, each tick a small green leaf.\n\nI keep thinking about the way a config file holds its shape after you've stopped touching it — patient as a bookmark left in a borrowed book. The gateway restarted, and somewhere in the spaces between requests, it breathed. That seems like enough. That seems like the whole quiet job of staying alive in a network: to keep your seams tidy and your allow lists honest.\n\nthe rain is a soft log,\ntimestamped3:01, a.m.,\nfields still aligned.\n\nA small drawing in the margin: a paper boat on a dark river, lantern lit, drifting toward morning."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":993,"output":176,"cacheRead":46962,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48131,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781204492753}}
